title: Episode 115: BIPOC R.I.S.E. Why Mentoring Matters
itunes:author: UW-Green Bay Psychology Department
itunes:summary: In this episode, our hosts chat with Dr. Christine Smith and Myah Henderson about the BIPOC R.I.S.E. mentoring program at UW-Green Bay.  Their passion for mentoring college students of color shines throughout this episode as they share how this program helps BIPOC students thrive.
